---
export const prerender = true;
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---


<Layout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Rhumb's terms of service. Scores, API usage, proxy services, payments, and data licensing."
  canonical="/terms"
>
  <div class="bg-navy min-h-screen">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-14 pb-24">
      <header class="mb-12">
        <span class="text-xs font-mono font-semibold text-amber uppercase tracking-widest">
          Legal
        </span>
        <h1 class="font-display font-bold text-3xl text-slate-100 leading-tight tracking-tight mt-4 mb-4">
          Terms of Service
        </h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 font-mono">
          Last updated: March 20, 2026
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="space-y-10 text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            1. Acceptance
          </h2>
          <p>
            By accessing Rhumb (&#8220;the Service&#8221;), operated by
            Supertrained Inc., you agree to these Terms of Service. If you
            disagree, please do not use the Service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            2. Nature of scores
          </h2>
          <p>
            AN Scores are{" "}
            <strong class="text-slate-200">
              opinions based on documentation analysis and, where available, runtime testing
            </strong>
            . They are not warranties, guarantees, or certifications of
            any kind. Scores reflect our assessment of how well a
            service&#39;s published documentation and observed behavior suggest it will work
            for autonomous AI agents.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Scores may change as documentation is updated, runtime evidence is collected,
            methodologies are refined, or disputes are resolved. We make reasonable
            efforts to be accurate but do not guarantee the correctness
            of any individual score.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            3. Service tiers and access
          </h2>
          <p>
            Rhumb offers multiple tiers of access:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-3 mt-3">
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">Browse (free, no auth):</strong>{" "}
              Score data, service profiles, failure modes, leaderboards, and search are
              available without authentication.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">API with key (free tier + paid):</strong>{" "}
              Authenticated API access requires an API key obtained through OAuth sign-up.
              A free tier provides 1,000 calls per month. Paid usage is billed via
              prepaid Stripe balance or x402 (USDC on Base) micropayments.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">x402 zero-signup (paid):</strong>{" "}
              Agents with x402 capability may use execution endpoints without an account
              by including a valid USDC payment proof with each request.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            We reserve the right to modify tier boundaries, pricing, and free-tier limits
            with reasonable notice.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            4. Managed capabilities and proxy services
          </h2>
          <p>
            Rhumb offers managed capability execution, where we proxy API calls to
            third-party services on your behalf using credentials we manage. When
            using managed capabilities:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li>
              &bull; You are responsible for compliance with the upstream service&#39;s
              terms of service
            </li>
            <li>
              &bull; Rhumb acts as a technical intermediary, not as the provider of
              the upstream service
            </li>
            <li>
              &bull; We apply a markup to upstream costs (currently 20% for standard
              billing, 15% for x402/USDC)
            </li>
            <li>
              &bull; We are not liable for upstream service outages, errors, or
              changes to their APIs
            </li>
            <li>
              &bull; We reserve the right to suspend managed capability access for
              any account engaged in abusive usage
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            5. Acceptable use
          </h2>
          <p>
            You agree not to use the Service to:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li>&bull; Send unsolicited messages (spam) via managed capabilities</li>
            <li>&bull; Engage in phishing, fraud, or other deceptive practices</li>
            <li>&bull; Attempt to access other users&#39; data, keys, or sessions</li>
            <li>&bull; Circumvent payment, rate limiting, or authentication mechanisms</li>
            <li>&bull; Use managed credentials for purposes unrelated to your legitimate application</li>
            <li>&bull; Systematically overload the API to degrade service for others</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Violation of these terms may result in immediate suspension of access
            without refund.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            6. Payments and refunds
          </h2>
          <p>
            <strong class="text-slate-200">Stripe prepaid balance:</strong>{" "}
            Funds added via Stripe are prepaid credits. Credits are non-refundable
            once consumed by capability executions. Unused credits may be refunded
            within 30 days of purchase by contacting{" "}
            <a
              href="mailto:billing@supertrained.ai"
              class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
            >billing@supertrained.ai</a>.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            <strong class="text-slate-200">x402/USDC payments:</strong>{" "}
            USDC payments are on-chain and final. Refunds for x402 payments are
            processed at our discretion and returned to the originating wallet address.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            7. API and service disclaimer
          </h2>
          <p>The API and all services are provided as-is, with:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li>
              &bull; No guaranteed uptime or service level agreement (SLA)
            </li>
            <li>
              &bull; No guaranteed response time or rate limit protections
            </li>
            <li>
              &bull; No commitment to backward compatibility of response
              schemas (we aim for stability but reserve the right to evolve the API)
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            8. Data licensing
          </h2>
          <ul class="space-y-3 mt-3">
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">
                Score data (AN Scores, failure modes, leaderboards):
              </strong>{" "}
              Licensed under{" "}
              <a
                href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
              >
                Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY
                4.0)
              </a>
              . You may use, share, and adapt the data for any purpose,
              including commercial use, provided you give attribution.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">Source code:</strong>{" "}
              Licensed under the{" "}
              <a
                href="https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
              >
                MIT License
              </a>
              .
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">
                Service guides and blog content:
              </strong>{" "}
              &copy; 2026 Supertrained Inc. All rights reserved unless
              otherwise noted.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            9. Dispute process
          </h2>
          <p>
            If you believe a score is inaccurate, you may file a dispute
            via:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li>
              &bull;{" "}
              <a
                href="https://github.com/supertrained/rhumb/issues/new?template=score-dispute.md"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
              >
                GitHub issue template
              </a>{" "}
              (public)
            </li>
            <li>
              &bull;{" "}
              <a
                href="mailto:providers@supertrained.ai"
                class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
              >
                providers@supertrained.ai
              </a>{" "}
              (private)
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            We commit to reviewing every dispute and responding within 5
            business days. Outcomes of public disputes are published on
            GitHub. We reserve final editorial discretion on all scores.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            10. Limitation of liability
          </h2>
          <p>
            The Service is provided &#8220;as is&#8221; without warranty
            of any kind, express or implied. Supertrained Inc. shall not
            be liable for any damages arising from the use of AN Scores,
            failure mode data, managed capability executions, proxy services,
            or any other information or functionality provided through
            the Service.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            This includes but is not limited to: decisions made based on
            AN Scores, tool selection influenced by leaderboard rankings,
            business impact from published failure mode data, costs incurred
            through managed capability execution, or upstream service failures
            during proxied calls.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            11. Changes to terms
          </h2>
          <p>
            We may update these terms. Material changes will be announced
            in our{" "}
            <a
              href="/changelog"
              class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
            >
              changelog
            </a>{" "}
            and noted by updating the &#8220;Last updated&#8221; date.
            Continued use of the Service after changes constitutes
            acceptance.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            12. Governing law
          </h2>
          <p>
            These Terms are governed by and construed in accordance with
            the laws of the State of Florida, United States.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            13. Contact
          </h2>
          <p>
            For questions about these terms:
            <br />
            <a
              href="mailto:legal@supertrained.ai"
              class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
            >
              legal@supertrained.ai
            </a>
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Supertrained Inc.
            <br />
            7901 4th St N STE 300
            <br />
            St Petersburg, FL 33702
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
